{"type":"miscellaneous","title":"Large Gems","summaries":["<b>Large Gems</b> are items designed for the <linked>PvP</linked> game <linked>Capture the Gem</linked>, and are dropped when the player <linked>dies</linked>, even if they are in <linked>Classic or Softcore mode</linked>. With each different Large Gem that is held or carried in the player's inventory, a hologram of it appears above the player's head. If two or more different Large Gems are carried, their holograms will revolve in a circular pattern above the player's head. They are immediately deleted if placed in a player's <linked>trash slot</linked>.","Large Gems can be placed into a <linked>Gem Lock</linked> to function as a key. This is primarily used in making adventure maps.","Each Large Gem can also be combined with a <linked>Minecart</linked> at any <linked>Anvil</linked> to produce a Gem Minecart. The Gem Minecarts are mechanically identical to the regular Minecart, but are aesthetically representative of their Gem type, and sparkle."],"statistics":{"Tooltip":"<i><span class=\"gameText\">For Capture the Gem. It drops when you die</span></i>","Rarity":"<span class=\"rarity\"><linked>[img:Rarity level: 1]</linked></span>","Sell":"No value","Research":"<abbr class=\"journey\" title=\"Journey Mode\">1 required</abbr>"},"crafts":{"Recipes":[{"result":{"rowspan":1,"value":"<span class=\"i -w multi-line\">[img:Large Amber]<span><span title=\"Large Amber\">Large Amber</span><span class=\"eico s i1 i2 i4 i6\" title=\"Desktop, Console, Mobile and Legacy tModLoader versions\"><b></b><i></i></span><div class=\"id\">Internal <linked>Item ID</linked>: 3643</div></span></span>"},"ingredients":{"value":"<ul><li><span class=\"i\"><linked>[img:Amber]</linked><span><span><linked>Amber</linked></span></span></span> <span class=\"note-text\">(15)</span></li></ul>"},"station":{"rowspan":7,"value":"<span class=\"i\"><linked>[img:Iron Anvil]</linked><span><span><linked>Iron Anvil</linked></span></span></span><br><i><b>or